 Sergeant Louise Lucas , 41 , was off-duty and on a shopping trip with her eight-year-old daughter Olivia in Swansea , South Wales , when she was struck as they tried to cross The Kingsway - a busy road .
Sgt Lucas managed to push her daughter to safety and she later died .
Police officers of all ranks paid their respects at her funeral at Christ Parish Church in Cyncoed , Cardiff .